(C) How to print a formatted table 
with while, for, and different data types

In the following C program, add a line that prints first fahrenheit, 
then a tab, then celsius, then a newline. Then change fahr and celsius
so that they are floats (and try printing then). Then print the values
from -20 to 120 counting by 10s. Finally, rewrite the 'while' loop with
a 'for' loop and remove all variables except fahr. Ensure the field
type characters are correct throughout (so, no error messages!).

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int fahr, celsius;
    int lower, upper, step;
    lower = 0;    /* lower limit of temperature table */
    upper = 300;  /* upper limit */
    step = 20;    /* step size */

    fahr = lower;
    while (fahr <= upper) {
        celsius = (5.0/9) * (fahr-32);
	/* fill in this line */
        fahr = fahr + step;
    }
}
